{
  "stem": "14251.5",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She had to find something to do so we had something to eat.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She managed to find Russian Jews-- first a couple that had a brand-new baby who were very religious evidently, which was forbidden by the communists already.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they could not keep me, because keeping you means also that you need to be fed and you need to have room, and they didn't even have enough for themselves.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Her father, I believe, was performing circumcisions on Jewish babies for people who still-- who had survived or who were from Russia, had moved forward from Russia, and wanted their children circumcised if they were Jews.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that was forbidden.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was a forbidden activity.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I remember this man when I had seen him-- and I had met that family, I got to be there once in a while-- hurrying in his coat and hat and-- and his satchel, like a doctor's little satchel.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Well, my mother had to find a place for me, and with the help of these Jewish people found this orphanage in which were the remnants of Jewish children of all ages where we were parked.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The trouble was that they took one look at me-- that wasn't so bad, the look.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But in the first conversation, they were just in a state of horror because they said, Nemetskiy, Nemetskiy, you know, as if I was faking my way into this orphanage, that I was German.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That means German in Russian.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That means German.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And most of us spoke Russian besides Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I-- I kept trying to say what it was, and I couldn't.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I didn't speak Yiddish, but it's similar to German.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It was a big mess.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I tried to explain.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "There was no one there to help me explain.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
